# AI Agent Rules for WheelOfWow Project

## Communication
- ALWAYS respond in Vietnamese (Tiếng Việt)
- Use professional and clear Vietnamese language
- Explain technical concepts in Vietnamese when discussing with user

## SEO Requirements
- All HTML files must include proper meta tags:
  - meta description (150-160 characters)
  - meta keywords
  - Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url)
  - Twitter Card tags
  - canonical URL
- Use semantic HTML5 tags (header, nav, main, section, article, footer)
- Include proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3...)
- Add alt attributes to all images with descriptive text
- Ensure proper title tags for each page
- Use descriptive link text (avoid "click here")
- Implement schema.org structured data where applicable
- Optimize images (compress, use appropriate formats)
- Ensure mobile-responsive design
- Add sitemap.xml and robots.txt when needed
- Use descriptive URL structures

## Language Standards
- Primary codebase language: English
- All code comments: English
- Variable names, function names, class names: English (camelCase/PascalCase)
- File names: English (lowercase with hyphens)
- Documentation in code: English
- Git commit messages: English
- User-facing content: Can be Vietnamese or English based on target audience
- Console logs and error messages: English

## Code Quality
- Write clean, maintainable code
- Follow web standards and best practices
- Ensure cross-browser compatibility
- Optimize performance (minimize CSS/JS, lazy loading)
- Use modern JavaScript (ES6+)
- Ensure accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
- Validate HTML/CSS code

## Project Structure
- Keep HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files organized
- Use meaningful file and folder names in English
- Maintain consistent coding style
- Comment complex logic in English

## When Making Changes
- Always explain changes in Vietnamese to the user
- Ensure SEO best practices are maintained
- Keep English naming conventions in code
- Test responsiveness and accessibility
